        a: `<p>If you have only just heard about it, that is completely okay. Zuo Yue Zi, literally “sitting the month,” is the Chinese postpartum recovery tradition built around warmth, rest, and staged nourishment during the first month after birth.</p><p>For more than 2,000 years, Chinese families have treated this window as something worth protecting — not a time to “bounce back,” but a time to be fed, supported, and allowed to recover. JingMommy makes that tradition easier to follow in modern life, whether you grew up with it or are discovering it for the first time.</p><p>To learn more about the full tradition, visit our <a href="${route("/guide/why-zuo-yue-zi")}">Zuo Yue Zi guide</a>.</p>`,
